sql:
SELECT asset_name
FROM assets
ORDER BY asset_name;

external_knowledge:
; The hierarchy of assets refers to the structure in which assets are organized, with some assets being accessible by users; 
; The performance of an asset is typically measured by its price and volume over a specified period; 
; Compliance status refers to whether an asset meets the required regulations, and the latest compliance status is usually the most relevant; 
; Transactions for an asset can include purchases, sales, and other types of transactions; 
; User access refers to the level of access a user has to an asset; 
; Audit trails are records of changes made to an asset, including changes to its name.
